    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"1028125\">Ant S.</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/202961-General/topic/.5Bmeta.5D.20an.20advice.20channel.20for.20tips.2Ftricks.20we.20may.20stumble.20upon/near/580733040\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Is it possible to have a channel where users can share anything they stumble upon as a nice trick to work more efficiently with Isabelle. e.g. to prove that a locale is inconsistent, it seems like <code>lemma foo: False</code> and <code>sledgehammer</code> are a nice starting point</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I think you could add them here (in this topic) for a start and if demand proves to be high, we can think about creating a channel.</p>",
        "id": 581303684,
