        "timestamp": 1774341248
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>A general strategy for proofs by contraposition: </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Isabelle\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">lemma</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"P ⟹ Q\"</span>\n<span class=\"k\">proof</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"¬Q ⟹ ¬P\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c\">(* replace with your proof*)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"k\">then</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">show</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"P ⟹ Q\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">auto</span>\n<span class=\"k\">qed</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 583139324,
        "sender_full_name": "Ant S.",
        "timestamp": 1775079933
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And here's one cool way I found to do case analysis on a disjunction: </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Isabelle\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">lemma</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"C\"</span>\n<span class=\"k\">proof</span>\n<span class=\"c\">(* suppose you know `P \\/ Q ==&gt; C` *)</span>\n<span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"P \\/ Q\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n<span class=\"k\">then</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">show</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"C\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">proof</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">cases</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"P \\/ Q\"</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">erule</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">disjE</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n<span class=\"k\">qed</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 583139532,
        "sender_full_name": "Ant S.",
        "timestamp": 1775080025
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This generalizes better:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Isabelle\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">lemma</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"C\"</span>\n<span class=\"k\">proof</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span>\n<span class=\"c\">(* suppose you know `P \\/ Q ==&gt; C` *)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">consider</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"P\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">2</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"Q\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">then</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">show</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"C\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">proof</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">cases</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c\">(*use the proof outline here*)</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 583517628,
        "sender_full_name": "Mathias Fleury",
        "timestamp": 1775247722
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(you can have any number of cases and each case can contain several properties)</p>",
